This paper deals with optimization of data transmission in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI) and data structures (cs.DS). The proposed approach involves exploiting spatial-temporal correlation among sensor data, which is a machine learning (cs.LG) technique. The paper also discusses energy consumption, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
